


---

**Discovery**

**Infrastructure Discovery & Assessment**

**Technical Architecture / Discovery**
- Identify Current State Desktop Management Infrastructure & Tooling (Physical & Virtual)
- Identify Existing Authoritative Hardware Inventory Source
- Identify Existing Authoritative Software Inventory Source
- Identify Existing Software Usage Source (If Applicable)
- Identify Existing User List Source
- Identify User To Department Mapping Source
- Identify User To Location Mapping Source
- Identify Software License Information (Where Available)
- Identify Other Critical Information Repositories (e.g. Warranty dates)

**Milestone:** Build Initial Discovery Feed Diagram

**Data Gathering**

**Infrastructure**
- Gather current network topology / capacity data
- Gather storage data / capacity
- Gather current desktop management infrastructure topology / capacity data
- Document Virtual Infrastructure & Usage

**Software & Hardware**
- Determine What Is An Application (MECM Application / Package / Installed Binary / Executable)
- Procure Software Inventory / Usage Tracking Tools (if required)
- Build Supporting Server Infrastructure For Inventory / Usage Tool
- Install Inventory / Application Usage Tool To Server Infrastructure
- Deploy Desktop Agent For Hardware & Software Discovery
- Deploy Desktop Agent For Software Usage Metering (if required)
- Gather Hardware Inventory Data
- Gather Software Inventory Data
- Identify Application Owners & Document
- Gather Software Usage Data (if applicable)
- Gather Software License Data (if applicable)
- Gather Peripheral Data

